<p><code>A:</code> It was the same for me actually. But then you should have made <em>Patlabor</em> yourself. Like the Griphone one.</p>
<p><code>I:</code> That, I did the script, even the conte [continuity?].</p>
<p><code>A:</code> Not only the conte, you should have directed the whole thing. The directorâ€™s job is just to take responsibility. Do it, before you get old.</p>
<p><code>I:</code> I tried to take responsibility. If it fails, itâ€™s my responsibility. If it succeeds, itâ€™s thanks to the staff.</p>
<p><code>A:</code> Yeah, thatâ€™s the ground rule. But you Mr.Â Izubuchi are still young, so youâ€™ll be OK.</p>
<p><code>I:</code> What are you talking about? Is that what you say to an elder?</p>
<p><code>A:</code> All I want to see is Bucchan having a rough time!! (laugh).</p>
<p>â€” Mr.Â Izubuchi, did you actually have a hard time?</p>
